Assistant: This component describes how social a person is. It ranges from being very reserved and quiet to being very outgoing and sociable.
This component shows how much a person uses their imagination versus being practical. It goes from being highly imaginative to being very grounded in reality.
This component identifies people who are typically quiet and thoughtful (reserved), and also very organized, responsible, and careful (conscientious).
This component describes people who are outgoing and sociable (extroverted), but also spontaneous, less inhibited, and willing to try new things (unconstrained).
This component relates to how curious and analytical a person is, and their interest in learning and complex ideas.
This component refers to how well a person interacts with others, builds relationships, and handles social situations.
This component describes someone who is generally relaxed, calm, flexible, and not easily stressed or bothered by small things.
This component highlights people who are very organized and responsible (conscientious), but also tend to be quiet or private (reserved). They are thorough but not always outgoing.
